title: Maxar acquires another tech company as it pursues growth in gaming and media
summary: Maxar is looking to turn its satellite imagery archive into new 3D products for gaming, media and other industries

title: Space Force lays out timeline for 2023 rapid-response launch experiment
summary: The Space Force's 'Space Safari' office is laying out a timeline for a tactically responsive launch mission projected to launch in 2023

summary: A day after revealing the completion of the 200th Falcon upper stage and Merlin Vacuum engine, SpaceX has announced that it also...

title: German team wins $5 million ANA Avatar XPrize in space-themed competition
summary: Germany’s Team NimbRo took home the $5 million grand prize in the ANA Avatar XPrize finals Nov. 5, after completing a test course that showed how remote-control robots could contribute to space exploration.

title: Psyche review finds institutional problems at JPL
summary: An independent review of problems that delayed the launch of NASA’s Psyche asteroid mission uncovered institutional issues at the Jet Propulsion Laboratory that led the agency to delay the launch of another mission being developed there.

title: Cygnus mission control fire alarm scrubs NG-18 launch for 24 hours
summary: Northrop Grumman was preparing to launch the second to last Antares 230+ rocket from Wallops Island, Virginia for the NG-18 mission to the International Space Station (ISS) at 5:50 AM EST (10:50 UTC) on Sunday, Nov. 6; however, a fire alarm in Cygnus’ mission control center initially pushed the launch to 5:55 AM EST, the end of the window, before eventually scrubbing the launch for the day.

title: Northrop Grumman ready for space station resupply mission
summary: Northrop Grumman is set to launch the penultimate flight of its current Antares rocket configuration — with Russian engines and a Ukrainian first stage structure — to begin a resupply mission Sunday delivering more than four tons of cargo to the International Space Station.

title: NASA, USAID Partnership Strengthens Global Development
summary: NASA and the U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID) signed an agreement Friday strengthening the collaboration between the two agencies, including efforts that advance the federal response to climate change.

title: Rocket Lab launches Swedish satellite, fails to catch booster
summary: Rocket Lab successfully launched a Swedish atmospheric science satellite on an Electron rocket Nov. 4, but a telemetry problem kept the company from attempting a mid-air recovery of the rocket’s booster.

title: NASA’s Artemis 1 moon rocket back on pad 39B for nighttime launch attempt
summary: NASA’s Space Launch System moon rocket arrived back on its Florida launch pad Friday, ready for a series of overnight launch opportunities beginning Nov. 14 to begin a crucial, long-delayed test flight that officials hope will set the stage for future lunar missions with astronauts.
